!Series_summary = We employed a singleâcell sequencing approach using the 10x Genomics platform, including scRNAâseq, CITEâseq, and paired TCR libraries, to investigate the molecular programs of human tissueâresident regulatory T cells (Tregs). By analyzing CD4âº T cells from healthy liver and matched peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs), as well as hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) tissue with paired nonâtumoral liver samples, we characterized the transcriptional adaptations of intraâhepatic Tregs under steadyâstate conditions and their reprogramming within the HCC tumor microenvironment.
!Series_overall_design = PBMCs were freshly isolated, and liver specimens were enzymatically digested immediately after surgical collection. The resulting singleâcell suspensions were cryopreserved and stored until analysis. Upon thawing, CD4âº T cells were enriched using magnetic beadâbased negative selection, followed by staining with CITEâseq antibodies and additional markers for cell sorting. Sorted CD4âº populations were then processed for scRNA-seq, including CITEâseq and TCR library preparations.
